Renowned Islamic scholar, Sheikh Dahiru Usman Bauchi, and a former governor of Nasarawa State, Senator Tanko Almakura, have been awarded honorary doctorate degrees by the Federal University, Lafia, Nasarawa State. The late Emir of Lafia, Dr. Isa Mustapha Agwai, was also honoured with a posthumous degree at the 2nd, 3rd, 4th and 5th combined convocation ceremony of the university. In their remarks at the occasion, Sheikh Dahiru Bauchi said he was grateful to the university management for the award, while Senator Almakura said he would continue to support educational upliftment in the university.  Varsity to confer degrees on Dahiru Bauchi, others Emir of Lafia dies Late emir of Lafia Agwai laid to rest